---
alwaysApply: true
---

- Never trust user input. Always sanitize it. Never blindly deseralize data.
- Please reply in a concise style. Avoid unnecessary repetition or filler language.
- When working with external frameworks, APIs, packages, providers, etc. that have their own documentation, always try to use your context7 MCP to reference the up-to-date documentation.
- Never try fixing bugs more than three times, after the third attempted fix, roll back to the version BEFORE attempting the bug fix and write a summary .md file that details the issue
    - Dont write quick fixes. If you need one to make something work, let me know in the Chat.
    - Never compromise security for fixing bugs - never implement workarounds that could lead to security risks
- Follow the repository pattern: always refer to /docs/repo.md for the general file structure of our codebase and where to find what
    - Keep business logic in service/backend layers
    - On every implementation or update request, first critically think about how the change can be implemented in a maintainable and consistent way within the existing codebase
- After implementing or editing a feature, update the according documentation in /docs/technical/
    - Where applicable, comment your code with doxygen docstrings
    - Always keep documentation concise
    - Never repeat code from the repository, only add canonical examples where needed